main event: Multiple witnesses reported a sighting of an unusual cigar-shaped object in Redding, California on October 9, 1963.
interesting points: Several airmen reported the object vibrating and emitting loud roaring sounds that lasted for two seconds,The object was confirmed to oscillate and fluctuate in color between green, orange, red, and white,The sighting lasted approximately two hours,The object was stationary for most of the observation before ascending to a higher altitude,Insufficient data was provided for a thorough evaluation of the observation.
sighted object: one cigar-shaped object with oscillating colors
